  "prompt": "Can European citizens live and work in the Bahamas?",
  "response": "European citizens cannot automatically live and work in the Bahamas without meeting specific immigration requirements. The Bahamas has its own immigration laws and policies, which apply to all foreign nationals, including Europeans. Here\u2019s what you need to know:\n\n1. **Tourist Visas**: European Union (EU) citizens visiting the Bahamas for tourism typically do not need a visa for stays of up to 90 days. However, this does not permit them to work.\n\n2. **Work Permits**: To work in the Bahamas, European citizens must obtain a work permit. This requires a job offer from a Bahamian employer, who usually sponsors the work permit application. The process involves demonstrating that the job cannot be filled by a Bahamian citizen or resident.\n\n3. **Residency Permits**: For long-term stays, European citizens may need to apply for residency permits. This can be based on employment, investment, or retirement, depending on individual circumstances.\n\n4. **Citizenship or Permanent Residency**: Living and working in the Bahamas indefinitely is only possible through obtaining citizenship or permanent residency, which involves strict criteria and is not guaranteed.\n\nIt\u2019s essential to consult the Bahamas\u2019 Department of Immigration or an immigration lawyer for the most up-to-date and accurate information tailored to your situation.",
